docs {
  # Create Analysis Job

  Creates a new analysis job for a given URL. The server will:
  1. Check for cached results (within 24 hours)
  2. Create a new job if no cache exists
  3. Queue the job for processing
  4. Return the job ID and status URL

  ## Request Body
  - `url` (required): The URL to analyze (max 2048 chars)
  - `analysisType` (optional): Type of analysis. Options:
    - `comprehensive` (default)
    - `seo`
    - `content`
    - `technical`

  ## Response
  Returns 202 Accepted with:
  - `jobId`: ID to check job status
  - `status`: Current status (PENDING)
  - `statusUrl`: URL to check job status

  ## Example URLs to test:
  - https://www.apple.com/legal/internet-services/terms/site.html
  - https://policies.google.com/terms
  - https://www.spotify.com/us/legal/end-user-agreement/
}
